I"<p>Helper classes are helpful for templating.</p>

<h3>Vertical Center</h3>
<p>Vertically center an element with the <code>vertical-center</code> class. (Uses <a href="http://caniuse.com/#search=flexbox" target="_blank">Flexbox</a>.)</p>

<div class="language-html highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nt">&lt;div</span> <span class="na">class=</span><span class="s">"vertical-center"</span><span class="nt">&gt;</span>
  <span class="nt">&lt;div&gt;</span>Vertically centered<span class="nt">&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="nt">&lt;/div&gt;</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<div class="vertical-center">
  <div>Vertically centered</div>
</div>

<h3>Text Alignment</h3>
<p>Use <code>text-left</code>, <code>text-right</code>, and <code>text-center</code> to align content.</p>

<div class="language-html highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nt">&lt;p</span> <span class="na">class=</span><span class="s">"text-left"</span><span class="nt">&gt;</span>Left<span class="nt">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="nt">&lt;p</span> <span class="na">class=</span><span class="s">"text-center"</span><span class="nt">&gt;</span>Center<span class="nt">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="nt">&lt;p</span> <span class="na">class=</span><span class="s">"text-right"</span><span class="nt">&gt;</span>Right<span class="nt">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<p class="text-left">
  <span class="example" style="padding: 5px;">Left</span>
</p>
<p class="text-center">
  <span class="example" style="padding: 5px;">Center</span>
</p>
<p class="text-right">
  <span class="example" style="padding: 5px;">Right</span>
</p>

<h3>Screen Reader Text</h3>
<p>Accessibility is important - if you have a label that should be hidden but accessible, or use an icon as a link, or want to skip navigation, use the <code>screen-reader-text</code> class to hide content visually.</p>

<div class="language-html highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nt">&lt;a</span> <span class="na">class=</span><span class="s">"screen-reader-text"</span> <span class="na">href=</span><span class="s">"#content"</span><span class="nt">&gt;</span>Skip Navigation<span class="nt">&lt;/a&gt;</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<h3>Responsive Images</h3>
<p>Add a <code>responsive-image</code> class for responsive images.</p>

<div class="language-html highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nt">&lt;img</span> <span class="na">src=</span><span class="s">"#"</span> <span class="na">class=</span><span class="s">"responsive-image"</span> <span class="na">alt=</span><span class="s">"Responsive Image"</span><span class="nt">&gt;</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<p><img src="https://placehold.it/1000x100" class="responsive-image" alt="Example of responsive-image CSS class" /></p>

